post_text: Who feels like cooking after a long, relaxing weekend anyway? Pick up dinner tonight from Chipotle to support the PTA!
shared_text:
Maercker PTA
September 8 at 7:38 AM ·

🌮🌯🌮 TONIGHT! Benefit Night - Chipotle 🌮🌯

🌮Every month the PTA partners with a local establishment to raise money for both the restaurant and Maercker PTA. Our first benefit night of the 2020-21 school year is at Chipotle in Willowbrook on Tuesday, Sept. 8th from 4:00-8:00 pm!

🌮Present the flyer below at checkout and Maercker PTA will receive 33% of the proceeds. There's also instructions on how to download and use the Chipotle app to order online.

🌮 If you use the app please don't forget to type District 60's online code 93YL7XB into the promo code section and then click "apply".

🌮If you download an e-gift certificate for Chipotle on the RaiseRight app, you can use that to pay for your food and Maercker PTA gets and extra 10% back!

post_text:
On January 29th, Wilbert Chu participated in the Chicago area American Regions Math League tryout and qualified for the Chicago All Star A/B Math Team for ARML. There were a total of 185 students in the tryout from various local high school teams. Wilbert scored 23 out of 24 (24 being the highest score) and made the Chicago ARML all star A/B team!

There were only 3 high school students who scored the full score of 24, who are high school upperclassmen. The cut off score for the A/B team is 21. Chicago ARML announced the top 30 scorers (who scored 21 and above) for the all star A/B team and Wilbert is one of them!

As Wilbert is an eighth grader, beating out/matching contestants from high schools strong in math except the 3 full scorers, this is a great privilege! Kudos to Wilbert!

#D60Learns #D60Excels

post_text:
8th graders have been learning about the importance and privileges of our First Amendment Rights. They have discussed how and why people speak up about their beliefs, stand up for their rights, protest, write, or even sing about important issues that our world faces today.

In ELA, students chose a “song of revolution” to analyze, research, and discuss. This project was related to our month’s theme of literacy in celebration of Academic Writing Month.

We'd like to recognize the following students and their standout projects - Manuela Nofodji, who studied the song ‘Be Free’ by J.Cole and learned about modern day civil rights, Sebrina Sebastian, who studied the song ‘Hijabi’ by Mona Haydar and learned about women’s rights, Christian Membrila-Ruiz, who studied the song ‘Mi Gente’ by J.Balvin, Willy William, & Beyonce and learned about diversity.

#D60Learns #AcademicWritingMonth
